        <num>CC 1519.1</num>
        <heading>1519.1. Penalty clauses</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1519.1. Penalty clauses
A provision in a juridical act that purports to penalize a person for filing an action to
challenge an inter vivos or mortis causa donation, an action related to a succession, or an
action related to a trust administration is unenforceable if, at the time of instituting the action
to challenge, a factual basis existed that would lead a reasonable person to conclude that
there is a substantial likelihood that the challenge would be successful.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=1428927</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
